articles.title: Japan counts down to ‘Moon Sniper’ landing on lunar surface - Al Jazeera English
articles.description: A successful touchdown will make Japan the fifth country ever to put a spacecraft on the moon.
articles.content:
Japan is attempting to land its high-precision Moon Sniper probe on the lunar surface and will become only the fifth country to put a spacecraft on the moon if all goes according to plan.
